# Monorepo lockfile agent gate (umbraculum-dev)

**Audience:** agents only. The operator is an analyst — **you** enforce lockfile policy; do not tell them to "avoid X in the future."

## Composer analogy (binding)

| PHP / Composer | npm / this repo |
|----------------|-----------------|
| `composer.json` | `package.json` — constraints |
| `composer.lock` | each committed `package-lock.json` — exact tree |
| `composer install` | `npm ci` / `npm run lock:install` — install from lock, **do not rewrite lock** |
| `composer update` | `npm install` / `npm run lock:update:*` — re-resolve, **rewrite lock** |

**Hard rule:** every **committed** `package-lock.json` must stay in git. If it changed locally, dependencies changed and tests ran on that tree — **commit lock + matching `package.json`** before push. Never `git restore` a lock alone and claim "reverted"; full revert is **`npm run lock:revert`** (restore lock from HEAD **and** reinstall `node_modules`).

## Committed lockfiles (always versioned)

- Root `package-lock.json` (includes `@umbraculum/api` workspace deps)
- `apps/web/package-lock.json`
- `apps/web/e2e/package-lock.json`
- `packages/platform/test-mcp/package-lock.json`
- `docs-site/vendor/brochure/package-lock.json`

## Forbidden (never commit)

**`services/api/package-lock.json`** — ephemeral bug artifact, not a SoT. API pins live in root lock. If on disk: **`rm -f services/api/package-lock.json`**.

## When agents MUST run the gate

Run skill **`monorepo-lockfile-gate`** when **any** of these apply:

| Trigger | Examples |
|---------|----------|
| Any tracked lockfile edit | root or `apps/web/package-lock.json` changed |
| Workspace dep bump | `package.json` under `apps/`, `services/`, `packages/` |
| Forbidden file present | `services/api/package-lock.json` on disk or staged |
| Pre-push with lockfile commit | commit touches any `package-lock.json` |
| CI symptom | GHA `npm ci` / lockfile sync failures |

**Skip** on pure docs-only prose with no manifest/lockfile surface (`apparatus: override` still valid).

## Agent commands (umbraculum-dev)

| Intent | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Install from locks (composer install) | `npm run lock:install` / `lock:install:root` / `lock:install:web` |
| Update locks (composer update) | `npm run lock:update:root` / `lock:update:web` — then test, commit json+lock |
| Full revert after accidental update | `npm run lock:revert` |
| Pre-commit gate | `npm run check:lockfiles` |
| Pre-push | clean tree + `npm run verify:pre-push` |

Use **`node:20-slim`** or compose **`web`** — not host npm for lock commits.

## Agent anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern | Why it fails |
|---|---|
| `git restore` lock without `npm ci` | `node_modules` still reflects accidental update — faulty tests |
| "Discard accidental lock" without fixing boot scripts | Procedure still runs composer update on every start |
| Commit host-only root lock regen | GHA `npm ci` rejects sync |
| `git add services/api/package-lock.json` | Forbidden |
| Tell operator to regen lockfile | **Agent** runs skill + commits |

